          <updateDate>2017-07-28T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Signing is Language Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 to: (1) include in the definition of "English learner" an individual whose native language is American Sign Language, and (2) count such individuals in the number of English learners in a state for the purpose of determining the amount of federal funds allotted&nbsp;to a state for English language programs.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2017-07-28</actionDate>
        </item>
